      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "the set of integers",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "stem:[bb(sf(Z)) = {..., -2, -1, 0, 1, 2, ...}]\n\nstem:[bb(sf(Z))** = {n in bb(sf(Z)) &#x2223; n != 0}]\n\nOther restrictions can be indicated in an obvious way, as shown below.\n\nstem:[bb(sf(Z))_(>-3) = {n in bb(sf(Z)) &#x2223; n > -3}]\n\nThe symbol stem:[ZZ] is also used.\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
